Both required outputs are emitted in the working directory:

- **`transcript.json`** — 20 iterations, 68 hypotheses, 68 analyses; conforms to `transcript_schema.json` (validated). Top-level fields `dataset_id` (`ds001_crc`), `model_id` (`claude-opus-4-7`), `harness_id`, `max_iterations` (25) all set. Each analysis includes signed `effect_estimate`, `p_value`, and `significant`.

- **`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative synthesis covering treatment main effects, biomarker main effects, canonical CRC treatment×biomarker interactions, prognostic baseline, sidedness, inflammation/nutrition labs, mets/symptoms/demographics/SNPs, and final multivariable models.

**Key findings.** Strong prognostic signals: ECOG (-1.17/unit), stage IV (-1.36 mo), albumin (+0.47/g/dL), weight loss (-0.07/%), KRAS (-0.36 mo), BRAF V600E (-0.36 mo), right-sided primary (-0.28 mo). Regorafenib has a robust positive main effect (+0.94 mo, p≈0) that survives multivariable adjustment. Notably, **all four canonical CRC biomarker–treatment interactions are null** (cetuximab×RAS-WT, encorafenib×BRAF V600E, pembrolizumab×MSI-H, trastuzumab+tucatinib×HER2-amplified), and age trends positive (older = longer PFS) — opposite the typical clinical expectation. Final OLS R² ≈ 0.84.
